<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 21 at 7:22AM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...INCREASED FIRE DANGER THIS AFTERNOON FOR SOUTHWEST VIRGINIA AND
SOUTHEAST WEST VIRGINIA...
Winds will be gusty this afternoon. Southwest winds 10 to 15 mph,
with gusts 20 mph can be expected. This combined with
humidity values dropping into the 20 to 30 percent range will
increase the risk for wildfire ignition and spread.
Residents are urged to exercise caution if handling any potential
ignition source, including machinery, cigarettes, and matches. Be
sure to properly discard all smoking materials. Any dry grasses,
dead leaves, and other tree litter that ignite will have the
potential to spread fire quickly.</description>
